, for example for $ {\\underline{M}}=RLLRC$ the curve $(\\alpha,\n{\\varphi}_{{\\underline{M}}}({\\alpha}))$ is not orthogonal to the diagonal. On\nthe other hand, for $ {\\underline{M}}=RLC$ it is. With different\nparametrization properties of equi-kneading maps for skew tent maps were\nconsidered by J.C. Marcuard, M. Misiurewicz and E. Visinescu.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Dec 2015 12:32:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 20 Apr 2016 08:17:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-21"}
