sure a small day- to night-side wind\nspeed of $(-1.7^{+1.1}_{-1.2})$ km/s. Compared to the recent detection of\nsodium blue-shifted by (8$\\pm$2) km/s, this likely implies a strong vertical\nwind shear between the pressures probed by near-infrared and optical\ntransmission spectroscopy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Dec 2015 14:06:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-03"}
